  <div class="tab-bar">
    <button class="tab active" data-tab="overview" onclick="showTab('overview')">Overview</button>
    <button class="tab" data-tab="academics" onclick="showTab('academics')">Academics</button>
    <button class="tab" data-tab="campus-life" onclick="showTab('campus-life')">Campus Life</button>
  </div>

  <!-- Tab Contents -->
  <div class="tab-content" id="overview-content">
    <div class="quick-facts">
      <h3>Quick Facts</h3>
      <div class="facts-grid">
        <div><p>Founded</p><strong>2013</strong></div>
        <div><p>Location</p><strong>Thimphu, Bhutan</strong></div>
        <div><p>Affiliation</p><strong>Royal Government of Bhutan</strong></div>
        <div><p>Students</p><strong>Data Not Available</strong></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-college">
      <h3>About Khesar Gyalpo University of Medical Sciences of Bhutan</h3>
      <p>
        The Khesar Gyalpo University of Medical Sciences of Bhutan (KGUMSB) was officially established in 2013. The university was renamed as the Khesar Gyalpo University of Medical Sciences of Bhutan by Her Gyaltsuen, The Queen of Bhutan, on 28th February 2015, honoring the King's efforts toward nation-building. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}
      </p>
      <p>
        KGUMSB is the first medical university in Bhutan, dedicated to training medical professionals such as doctors, nurses, and public health experts. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}
      </p>
      <p>
        The university comprises several faculties, including the Faculty of Nursing and Public Health (FNPH), Faculty of Postgraduate Medicine (FoPGM), Faculty of Traditional Medicine (FoTM), and Faculty of Undergraduate Medicine (FoUGM). :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tab-content hidden" id="academics-content">
    <h3>Academic Programs at KGUMSB</h3>

    <hr style="margin: 1.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />

    <h4>Undergraduate Programs</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS)</li>
      <li>Bachelor of Science in Nursing and Midwifery</li>
      <li>Bachelor of Science in Clinical Counseling</li>
      <li>Bachelor of Science in Traditional Medicine</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Postgraduate Programs</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Doctor of Medicine (MD) in various specializations</li>
      <li>Master of Public Health (MPH)</li>
      <li>Master of Science in Traditional Medicine</li>
    </ul>

    <hr style="margin: 1.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />

    <h4>Admission Information</h4>
    <p>
      Admissions for the academic year 2025 are open from 15th March to 30th March 2025. Applicants must have completed Class XII with relevant science subjects. Selection is based on merit ranking and program preferences. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}
    </p>

    <h4>Funding Options</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Royal Government of Bhutan Scholarships</li>
      <li>Self-Financed</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Ensure your personal details are accurate and your contact number remains active. You will receive a notification with your application number upon successful submission.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tab-content hidden" id="campus-life-content">
    <h3>Campus Life at KGUMSB</h3>
    <p>
      KGUMSB offers a vibrant campus life with facilities that include well-equipped laboratories, a comprehensive library, and various co-curricular activities. The university hosts seminars, conferences, and workshops to enhance the learning experience. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}
    </p>

    <div class="campus-gallery" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr)); gap: 10px; margin-top: 1rem;">
